# Allow-list approach: ignore everything, then allow specific config.
# Anything not explicitly un-ignored stays out of the repo (sessions, history,
# credentials, caches, telemetry, etc.).

/*
!/.gitignore
!/README.md
!/CLAUDE.md
!/skills/
!/agents/
!/commands/
!/output-styles/
!/settings.json

# Inside the allowed dirs, drop noisy files.
**/.DS_Store
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/node_modules/

# Credentials / local config for individual skills (do not commit).
# Each skill may keep its own .env (with API keys) and a checked-in .env.example.
**/.env
!**/.env.example
